<!-- \if — conditional block using TW5 <%if filter%>...<%endif%> shortcut (TW5 5.3+).
     Hawaiian equivalent: heihei (race/compete — multiple candidate bodies, first wins).
     lar-see-also: heihei

     <<~ \if filter >>body<<~/ \if >> renders body only when filter yields a non-empty result.
     Operator talk-story: TW5 filter semantics differ from imperative conditionals.
     The filter runs in the current tiddler context; true = at least one result.
     Use `[<variable>match[value]]` for equality, `[condition]` for existence tests.

     No mode= param — control flow has no projection posture. -->

\procedure ~\if(p1:"" p2:"")
<%if [<p1>]%>
<$transclude $variable="~" name=<<p2>>/>
<%endif%>
\end
